    "For instance, industrial by-products such as FA (Types C and F), slag cement, SF, and ground GGBFS are commonly used to improve concrete's sustainability.",
    "Additionally, agricultural by-products like RHA, POFA, and SCBA contribute to this effort by repurposing waste materials.",
    "Other SCMs include calcined clay and limestone, which play a significant role in enhancing concrete properties, though they don't fit into these traditional categories.",
    "Furthermore, some municipal waste products, such as recycled glass, is also being explored for their potential as SCMs.",
    "By utilizing these diverse materials, the concrete industry can reduce its reliance on traditional cement while repurposing waste, thereby mitigating environmental impact [3]."
